Preheat your #grill{} to high. Pop the @breast of chicken{2}(British) on a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle the @Za'atar{} spice over the chicken. Season with @salt{} and drizzle on a splash of @oil{}. Rub the flavours into the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Pop the baking tray under the grill. Grill the chicken until cooked through and golden, ~{15-18%minutes}, turning halfway.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is done when no longer pink in the middle!

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1}. Trim the @courgette{1}, quarter lengthways then chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a splash of oil in a #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90} and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the courgette, garlic and @ground cumin{1}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}, then add the @water{75}(for the sauce). Bring to the boil then stir in the @chicken stock paste{10} and lentils. Simmer until the courgette is tender stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When the chicken is ready, transfer to a #plate{}. Keep to one side.

Stir the @crème fraiche{100.05} into the lentils and bring to the boil. Season to taste with salt and @black pepper{}. Share the lentils between your #bowls{} and top with the chicken. Enjoy!

> Mod Step 4: If you've decided to add bacon lardons to your meal, add to the pan before you add the courgette, garlic and cumin and cook for 2 mins. Add the courgette, garlic and cumin to the bacon and cook as instructed.